docs.lead_paragraph: Mixed-price movements ruled throughout the bond market yesterday in slightly more active trading on the New York Stock Exchange. Domestic corporation loans worked irregularly lower under the leadership of public utility bonds, while United States Government obligations maintained a firm undertone both on the Stock Exchange and in the outside market.
